MORE people in Glasgow than ever before have registered to vote. Record number register to vote MORE people in Glasgow than ever before have registered to vote.In December 2009, 421,100 residents - 86% of the city's voting-age population - were on the electoral register.By December 2012, that figure had risen to 93%.Now, just days before people go to the polls to vote in the independence referendum, the number of people registered to vote has reached 97.2%, which is the highest ever level of registration in the city. 